<body>
		<segment id="1" parent="12" relname="span">There is a gardening revolution going on.</segment>
		<segment id="2" parent="11" relname="span">People are planting flower baskets with living plants,</segment>
		<segment id="3" parent="2" relname="elaboration">mixing many types in one container for a full summer of floral beauty.</segment>
		<segment id="4" parent="10" relname="purpose">To create your own "Victorian" bouquet of flowers,</segment>
		<segment id="5" parent="10" relname="span">choose varying shapes, sizes and forms, besides a variety of complementary colors.</segment>
		<segment id="6" parent="5" relname="elaboration">Plants that grow tall should be surrounded by smaller ones and filled with others that tumble over the side of a hanging basket.</segment>
		<segment id="7" parent="9" relname="span">Leaf textures and colors will also be important.</segment>
		<segment id="8" parent="7" relname="elaboration">There is the silver-white foliage of dusty miller, the feathery threads of lotus vine floating down from above, the deep greens, or chartreuse, even the widely varied foliage colors of the coleus.</segment>
